# https://claude.ai/chat/4c5210eb-496c-45a0-86fc-dfebfb9786c1
	Great setup! You've already got two key pieces covered - a quality conical fermenter and an all-in-one electric brewing system. Here's what else you'll need to start brewing:
	Essential Equipment Still Needed
	Cleaning & Sanitization

	PBW or OxiClean Free (for cleaning)
	Star San or Iodophor (no-rinse sanitizer)
	Carboy/fermenter brush
	Soft-bristle cleaning brushes

	Measuring & Testing

	Hydrometer or refractometer (measure gravity/ABV)
	Thermometer (if not built into your VEVOR system)
	pH meter or strips (optional but helpful)
	Kitchen scale (for hops and small additions)

	Fermentation Management

	Blow-off tube setup (for high krausen)
	Fermentation temperature control (chest freezer + temp controller, or fermentation chamber)
	CO2 tank and regulator (for pressure fermentation with your Fermzilla)

	Bottling OR Kegging Setup
	If Bottling:

	Bottles (about 48-50 for a 5-gallon batch)
	Bottle capper and caps
	Bottling wand/filler
	Priming sugar

	If Kegging:

	Cornelius kegs (ball lock or pin lock)
	CO2 tank and regulator (if not already purchased for fermentation)
	Keg coupler/tap system
	Beer lines and faucets

	Ingredients & Consumables

	Brewing water (or water treatment salts if needed)
	Yeast nutrients (optional but recommended)
	Various hops, malts, and yeast for recipes

	Nice to Have

	Wort chiller (though your VEVOR's condensing coil may serve this purpose)
	Auto-siphon or transfer pump
	Extra silicone hoses and tri-clamp fittings
	Spare airlock
	Notebook or brewing software for recipe tracking

	Your VEVOR system should handle mashing, boiling, and initial wort chilling, while the Fermzilla is perfect for both standard and pressure fermentation. You're in excellent shape to start brewing!